This paper uses social media data to analyze attitudes towards immigration, which falls under the category of social issues. Therefore, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also uses natural language processing techniques to analyze the text data, which suggests that cs.CL (Computation and Language) is another likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses network structure, which could fall under cs.SOC (Social and Economic Networks) or cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity and Privacy). Finally, the paper uses semi-supervised topic modeling, which could also fall under cs.DL (Machine Learning).
